Package elements

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Alphabet
    Class which define all the possible values for a Praat parameter or several praat parameter (specify it in the name).
    It will be use in the class manipulating sequences to give a value in a specific interval to the parameter.
    Formant
    Class which define the structure of a formant and its attributes.
    Our program deal with sequences of formants, this structures are defined in FormantSequence.
    The FormantSequence class use this one.
    FormantSequence
    Class which define the structure of the sequence that will be analyze by the genetic algorithm
    The class is designed in order that once the number of formant is fixed, you cannot change it.
    GlobalAlphabet
    Class wich define the meta alphabet of the program.
    Sequence
    Class that define the structure of the basic element use in the run of the Ga.
    We call it Sequence in reference at the DNA sequence that is the general evoluting structure in a GA.
    This structure is used in all the classes related to the GeneticAlgorithmCall class (linked in the see also part).
    You aren't suppose to instantiate one yourself, the GA will do it for you with the SequenceFactory,
    This class only define the structure and the operations on it
